@startuml
title Safety Boundaries

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

package "Untrusted Planning Zone" {
  actor "User" as User
  component "AI Client / LLM\nplanner and explainer only" as Llm
}

package "Controlled Tool Boundary" {
  component "cli.py\nbounded commands" as Cli
  component "agent.py\nreview-first state machine" as Agent
  component "mcp_generator_server.py\nworkspace-bounded tools" as GeneratorMcp
  component "mcp_trino_server.py\nread-only Trino tools" as TrinoMcp
}

package "Deterministic Safety Core" {
  component "profiling/\nsafe metadata extraction" as Profiling
  component "generation/\nseeded synthetic rows" as Generation
  component "validation/\nexecutable checks" as Validation
  component "safety.py\nPII and row-copy guards" as Safety
  component "core/\nDatasetProfile + DatasetSpec" as CoreModels
}

package "External / Local Data" {
  database "Trino\nallowlisted read-only" as Trino
  folder "Source CSV\npotentially sensitive" as SourceCsv
  folder "Workspace\nprofiles, specs,\nreports, manifests" as Workspace
  folder "Generated Bundle\nsynthetic rows only" as Output
}

User --> Llm : intent
Llm --> Cli : safe CLI calls
Llm --> GeneratorMcp : MCP calls\nsummary responses
Cli --> Agent : agent-plan /\nagent-approve
Cli --> Profiling : direct profiling
Cli --> Generation : direct generation
Cli --> Validation : direct validation
Agent --> Profiling : plan phase
Agent --> Generation : approved phase
Agent --> Validation : approved phase
Agent --> Safety : source-row reuse check
GeneratorMcp --> Profiling : profile_csv
GeneratorMcp --> Generation : generate_dataset /\nexport_dataset
GeneratorMcp --> Validation : validate_dataset
TrinoMcp --> Trino : metadata, aggregates,\nmasked samples, bounded SELECT
Profiling --> SourceCsv : read locally for\nmetadata and distributions
Profiling --> CoreModels : DatasetProfile
Generation --> CoreModels : DatasetSpec
Validation --> CoreModels : DatasetSpec
Safety --> SourceCsv : compare only for\ncopy detection
Agent --> Workspace : request, plan,\nprofile, spec, result
GeneratorMcp --> Workspace : profile, spec,\nmanifest, report
Generation --> Output : write synthetic files
Validation --> Output : read generated files
Safety --> Output : compare generated files

note right of TrinoMcp
Rejects DDL/DML, unrestricted SELECT *,
multiple statements, joins, CTEs,
subqueries, ordering, and likely PII
aliases in safe-select mode.
end note

note right of Safety
Sensitive fields are treated as
sensitive by default. Raw production
rows must never become generated output.
end note

note bottom of Llm
The LLM boundary is intentional:
planning is advisory, while generation,
validation, and safety checks are
deterministic Python code.
end note

@enduml
